---
/**
 * P-legal: Cookie policy (EN). Заполнена по аудит-пакету (перевод; испанская версия
 * приоритетна). Кнопка отзыва согласия — через [data-cc-open] (C4/G2). Индексируется.
 */
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Crumbs from '../../components/Crumbs.astro';
import { OWNER, LEGAL_UPDATED_HUMAN } from '../../config/site';
import { ROUTES } from '../../lib/routes';
---

<Layout
  lang="en"
  title="Cookie policy | litcore.ai"
  description="Cookies used by litcore.ai: one technical cookie only; analytics only with consent. How to change or withdraw your choice."
  path="/en/cookies/"
  alternates={ROUTES.cookies}
>
  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container legal-page">
      <Crumbs lang="en" items={[{ label: 'HOME', href: '/en/' }, { label: 'COOKIES' }]} />
      <h1>Cookie policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        We use essential cookies only. Analytics runs only if you accept it in the banner.
      </p>
      <p class="mono small muted">Last updated: {LEGAL_UPDATED_HUMAN.en}</p>

      <p class="muted small">
        This is an English translation. The legally binding version is the Spanish{' '}
        <a href="/es/cookies/">Política de Cookies</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What cookies are</h2>
      <p>
        A cookie is a small file a website stores on your device to remember information about
        your visit. This policy explains which cookies litcore.ai uses and how to manage them,
        under art. 22.2 of Spain's LSSI, the GDPR and the AEPD cookie guidance.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Cookies we set today</h2>
      <p>
        The site currently sets <strong>one first-party technical cookie</strong> that remembers
        your banner choice. <strong>No analytics, advertising or third-party cookies.</strong>
      </p>
      <table class="lc">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Cookie</th>
            <th>Owner</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
            <th>Duration</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="mono">lc_consent</span></td>
            <td>litcore.ai (first-party)</td>
            <td>Technical / necessary</td>
            <td>
              Stores your cookie-banner choice (accept / decline). Exempt from consent as strictly
              necessary (art. 22.2 LSSI).
            </td>
            <td>180 days</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>3. Analytics and third-party cookies</h2>
      <p>There are <strong>none</strong> today. If we ever add analytics or other non-technical cookies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>they will run <strong>only after your consent</strong> in the banner (never before);</li>
        <li>
          we will list them in the table above (owner, purpose, duration) and, for providers
          outside the EEA, disclose the international transfer and its safeguard (see the{' '}
          <a href="/en/privacy/">Privacy policy</a>);
        </li>
        <li>you will be able to accept or decline them <strong>granularly</strong> (per purpose).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Legal basis</h2>
      <p>
        Non-technical cookies are set only with your <strong>consent</strong> (GDPR art. 6(1)(a)),
        given through a clear affirmative action in the banner. Continuing to browse or scrolling
        does <strong>not</strong> count as consent.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Changing or withdrawing your choice</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>On the site:</strong> change your choice at any time with the button below or via
        the “Cookie settings” link in the footer. Withdrawing consent is as easy as giving it.
      </p>
      <p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--ghost" data-cc-open>Cookie settings</button>
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>In your browser:</strong> you can block or delete cookies in your browser
        settings. If you delete the <span class="mono">lc_consent</span> cookie, the banner will
        appear again.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Consent duration</h2>
      <p>
        We remember your choice for 180 days, then ask again. We will also ask again if purposes
        change or new cookies are added.
      </p>

      <h2>7. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        While only the first-party technical cookie is used, there are <strong>no</strong>{' '}
        cookie-related international transfers. If providers outside the EEA are added, this will
        be disclosed here and in the Privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about cookies or data: <a href={`mailto:${OWNER.email}`}>{OWNER.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
